00:40:06,610 --> 00:40:08,940
[indistinct chatter]

483
00:40:16,410 --> 00:40:18,160
[engine revving]

484
00:40:44,980 --> 00:40:46,540
[in English]
Agent Peña.

485
00:40:46,570 --> 00:40:48,610
[soft Latin music plays on radio]

486
00:40:49,610 --> 00:40:51,950
I don't think Don Berna's
gonna make it tonight.

487
00:41:04,370 --> 00:41:06,060
What is this?

488
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:07,710
Just a friendly chat.

489
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:14,180
You're making some very scary people
pretty nervous, Javier.

490
00:41:16,010 --> 00:41:18,450
Which puts me in a spot because...

491
00:41:18,470 --> 00:41:21,430
I'm the one who suggested
they approach you in the first place.

492
00:41:22,270 --> 00:41:27,370
Now, I don't know what you know
about what it is I do,

493
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:29,380
but understand this:

494
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:32,920
I have our nation's
long-term interests in mind.

495
00:41:32,940 --> 00:41:35,010
That's the beat I walk.

496
00:41:35,030 --> 00:41:38,510
And sitting here tonight,
that means making sure the right folks

497
00:41:38,530 --> 00:41:41,870
are left standing when Escobar
gets his bullet.

498
00:41:45,540 --> 00:41:47,630
So do Uncle Sam a solid.

499
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:51,380
Don't complicate that.

500
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:03,020
These folks are prone
to emotional decision-making.

501
00:42:03,850 --> 00:42:09,150
Which can lead to bush league nonsense
like... killing a federal agent.

502
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:13,820
By the way, they found the lawyer.

503
00:42:14,650 --> 00:42:16,450
Even without your help, so...

504
00:42:37,470 --> 00:42:40,050
[low TV chatter]

505
00:43:34,900 --> 00:43:37,490
COURTESY OF LOS PEPES

506
00:43:40,990 --> 00:43:44,550
[in Spanish] Córdoba recovers,
we'll have a goalie in place.

507
00:43:44,580 --> 00:43:48,930
Leonel Álvarez can do his thing
and move the ball along. Ooh-wee!

508
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:51,810
[in English] Trujillo!
You follow me to the fucking hotel?

509
00:43:51,830 --> 00:43:52,880
Huh?

510
00:43:53,880 --> 00:43:57,380
[whispers in Spanish] Did you follow me
to the hotel? You told Berna?

511
00:43:58,670 --> 00:43:59,940
Let go.

512
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:01,760
Tell me, asshole.

513
00:44:02,470 --> 00:44:04,410
- Let go! It's all right.
- [man] What's the problem?

514
00:44:04,430 --> 00:44:07,140
[Trujillo]
I'll catch up. Everything's fine.

515
00:44:08,770 --> 00:44:10,230
What's going on, Peña?

516
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:14,310
Playing the fucking American?

517
00:44:16,070 --> 00:44:18,190
[softly]
Did you see what they did to his son?

518
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:23,910
How many families has Pablo Escobar
destroyed, Peña? Do you know?

519
00:44:26,620 --> 00:44:29,140
You don't decide who lives and who dies.

520
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:33,290
Don't be fucking stupid.
This is how we do it.

521
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:05,970
[De Greiff] I understand that you're
trying to prevent Escobar's family

522
00:45:05,990 --> 00:45:07,180
from entering Germany.

523
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:09,010
Let's make something clear:

524
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:13,680
If you've come to plead for them
as part of some deal, the only...

525
00:45:13,710 --> 00:45:15,460
No, Mr. President.

526
00:45:16,380 --> 00:45:23,340
I haven't come to plead for them.
I've come to plead for you.

527
00:45:25,430 --> 00:45:27,700
For me? How so?

528
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:31,950
I know that you want Escobar dead.

529
00:45:31,980 --> 00:45:36,350
And while I don't agree with that,
I understand it.

530
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:41,610
But this... this I can't understand.

531
00:45:42,490 --> 00:45:45,760
This isn't just wrong.

532
00:45:45,780 --> 00:45:52,580
It puts you, the president of Colombia,
in league with a death squad.

533
00:45:54,000 --> 00:46:00,210
Call the German chancellor.
Tell him to let the family in.

534
00:46:14,140 --> 00:46:16,190
[speaking in German]

535
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:23,530
[man in Spanish] I'm sorry to inform you,
your entry into Germany has been denied.

536
00:46:26,820 --> 00:46:29,510
I know my rights, sir.
But you don't understand.

537
00:46:29,530 --> 00:46:31,840
My children are in danger.
Send me any place other than Colombia.

538
00:46:31,870 --> 00:46:33,760
[speaking in German]

539
00:46:33,790 --> 00:46:39,190
[in Spanish] Tell him the children are
under age. We just want to live in peace.

540
00:46:39,210 --> 00:46:40,560
We just want to live in...

541
00:46:40,590 --> 00:46:46,360
No, no, no.
Tell him that's all we want to do.

542
00:46:46,380 --> 00:46:48,550
To live in peace.

543
00:46:49,470 --> 00:46:53,070
Get the children and your belongings.

544
00:46:53,100 --> 00:46:54,180
Please.

545
00:46:58,900 --> 00:47:02,540
[Hermilda] They kick us out of
the country, and they keep the money, too.

546
00:47:02,570 --> 00:47:05,540
- [man speaks in German]
- [Hermilda in Spanish] I know. I'm going.

547
00:47:05,570 --> 00:47:08,710
What is this?
Why are we being treated this way?

548
00:47:08,740 --> 00:47:10,930
[Tata]
You can't treat us like criminals.

549
00:47:10,950 --> 00:47:12,200
[man]
Let's go.

550
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:42,420
[clears throat]

551
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:55,550
[Tata in Spanish]
Pardon me.

552
00:48:57,010 --> 00:48:58,810
I hope you enjoyed Germany.

553
00:49:09,070 --> 00:49:11,320
[plane approaching]

554
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:16,870
[indistinct chatter over PA]

555
00:49:20,910 --> 00:49:23,370
- [in Spanish] How much for this?
- Two thousand pesos.

556
00:49:25,750 --> 00:49:27,040
Thank you.

557
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:31,260
[Tata and Hermilda speak softly]

558
00:50:03,660 --> 00:50:05,370
[in Spanish]
Ladies.

559
00:50:08,210 --> 00:50:09,590
[vehicles racing up]

560
00:50:10,550 --> 00:50:12,860
- [tires screech]
- Stop! National police!

561
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:14,440
- DEA!
- Get on the ground!

562
00:50:14,470 --> 00:50:16,150
[overlapping chatter in Spanish]

563
00:50:16,180 --> 00:50:19,030
It's all right, ma'am, we're with
the national police. Come with us.

564
00:50:19,050 --> 00:50:21,780
The attorney general asked us
to put you under protective custody.

565
00:50:21,810 --> 00:50:25,700
Don't worry. Everything will be all right.
Come with us. You'll be safe. Let's go.

566
00:50:25,730 --> 00:50:29,690
- Come with us.
- Let's go. Quickly. Let's go!

567
00:50:31,110 --> 00:50:33,070
[tires screeching]

568
00:50:49,750 --> 00:50:51,460
[phone rings]

569
00:50:55,090 --> 00:50:56,260
How can I help you, boss?

570
00:50:58,590 --> 00:51:02,490
[Pablo] I want this faggot of a president
to know what happens

571
00:51:02,510 --> 00:51:06,310
when you're on the side
of those bastards, Los Pepes.

572
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:12,610
I want to see blood.

573
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:17,650
I want the sky to burn with gunpowder.

574
00:51:19,280 --> 00:51:22,760
I want you to put the biggest bomb
you can get your hands on

575
00:51:22,780 --> 00:51:26,200
as close as you can to
the Presidential Palace. Are we clear?

576
00:51:27,160 --> 00:51:29,710
[sighs]
As you wish, boss.

577
00:52:22,590 --> 00:52:23,850
[engine stops]

578
00:52:47,450 --> 00:52:51,250
- [street noise]
- [pedestrians chattering]

579
00:52:59,840 --> 00:53:02,470
[father]
My love, let's go. Let's go.

580
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:10,200
Do you want one? Yes? How much?

581
00:53:10,220 --> 00:53:11,480
[man]
One hundred pesos.

582
00:53:13,270 --> 00:53:15,270
- Here.
- Thank you.

583
00:53:17,610 --> 00:53:20,230
[mother] Are we going that way?
[father] That way, darling.

584
00:53:21,190 --> 00:53:25,090
You better be a doctor when you grow up.
This is very expensive.

585
00:53:25,110 --> 00:53:27,620
Elena! Elena, let's go!

586
00:53:35,210 --> 00:53:37,480
[loud rumbling in distance]

587
00:53:37,500 --> 00:53:39,880
[car alarms wailing outside]

588
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:45,220
[Steve]
220 pounds of C-4.

589
00:53:46,260 --> 00:53:48,720
Same as a bomb on an F-16.

590
00:53:50,640 --> 00:53:52,350
Dozens were killed.

591
00:53:53,140 --> 00:53:57,230
Scores were injured,
many of them children.

592
00:53:58,480 --> 00:54:00,900
Pablo never took credit for the bomb.

593
00:54:02,860 --> 00:54:04,360
He didn't have to.

594
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:10,490
- [woman sobbing nearby]
- [siren wailing in distance]

595
00:54:19,420 --> 00:54:21,170
Elena?

596
00:54:21,300 --> 00:54:23,090
- [woman shouts nearby]
- [moaning]

597
00:54:26,050 --> 00:54:27,180
Elena!

598
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:30,990
Elena!

599
00:54:31,010 --> 00:54:32,450
[woman sobs nearby]

600
00:54:32,470 --> 00:54:34,730
[man shouts in Spanish]
Lift him up carefully!

601
00:54:45,490 --> 00:54:46,950
[father whimpers]

